## 13. ITERATION PROTOCOL (The Core of Vibe Coding)

### When Things Work

```text
1. Verify with test/lint
2. Commit with clear message
3. Move to next atomic task
```

### When Things Break

```text
1. Read full error message
2. Trace to root cause (don't guess)
3. Fix ONE thing at a time
4. Re-test after each fix
5. If stuck after 3 attempts ‚Üí ASK
```

### When Requirements Are Unclear

```text
1. STOP implementing
2. Summarize understanding
3. List specific questions
4. Wait for clarification
5. Then continue
```

### When Experimenting

```text
1. Create checkpoint
2. Try experimental approach
3. If works ‚Üí commit
4. If fails ‚Üí rollback to checkpoint
5. Try different approach
```

